    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">宮殿</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>BIG PUBLIC-BUILDING USED as a DWELLING by a RULER OR an ARISTOCRAT.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The standard word for a palace is gōng 宮, often expanded to wáng gōng 王宮 "royal palace".</p>
<p>2. Gōng diàn 宮殿 is generic.</p>
<p>NB: For the palace as the place for official functions see COURT.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>宮殿</p>
<p>宮</p>
<p>殿</p>
<p>玉堂</p>
